Peters has resigned from her role as a member of parliament (MP) for the ANC. According to News24, Peters handed in her resignation, which is effective immediately and was backdated to March 31. Peters was in the Western Cape to launch a road safety campaign when she heard from President Jacob Zuma that she had been fired. Her position has been filled by Joe Maswanganyi. Last week, Peters wrote on Facebook that she had bowed out with her integrity still intact. See the full post below. ALSO READ: Cheryl Carolus imagined ANC committee s call for Zuma to resign Mantashe For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.